COPY CAT CINNABON RECIPE
(Makes 12)
Dough:
2¼ teaspoon active dry yeast
1 cup milk (warmed)
½ cup granulated sugar
⅓ cup butter
1 teaspoon salt
2 eggs
4 cups all-purpose flour

Filling:
1 cup brown sugar
3 tablespoons cinnamon 
⅓ cup butter

Cream cheese icing:
6 tablespoons butter
1½ cups powdered sugar
¼ cup cream cheese (at room temp)
½ teaspoon vanilla extract
⅛ teaspoon salt

Directions:
* Dissolve the yeast in the warm milk with a teaspoon of sugar. Let it sit for about 5 minutes or until it starts to froth up. 
* To the bowl of your mixer add the sugar, butter, salt, eggs, and flour. Next, pour in the yeast mixture and mix well. 
* Place the dough into an oiled bowl, cover and let rise for about 1 hour. 
* Grease a baking dish with cooking spray. Combine the brown sugar and cinnamon in a bowl. 
* Roll the dough out. Spread the butter evenly over the dough, then sprinkle with the sugar evenly over the surface of the dough. Roll the dough down to the bottom of the other edge. 
* Cut the roll into 1½ inch slices, and place in a lightly greased baking pan. You can also use floss to cut into slices, as seen in the video.  
* Place the rolls in the pan. Cover with a clean kitchen towel or plastic wrap and let them rise for 30 minutes. 
* Preheat oven to 350°F.  
* Place the baking pan in the oven and bake for 25 minutes or until golden brown!

One of my favorite drills to work on tag plays and glove work around the bag!

- Staying in a neutral position to be prepared for good or bad throw
- Having to read the ball and adjust based on the direction and hop
- Receiving the ball as deep as possible (because the ball travels faster to you rather than you going out to go get it)
- Focusing on a quick tag in front of the base
